/*!
    \page ai-assistant-setup.html
    \sa {AI assistant},{AI models},{MCP servers},{Using the AI assistant}
    \title Setting up the AI assistant

    \section1 Before you start

    To use the AI assistant in \QDS, you need an API key to Gemini, OpenAI, or Claude.

    \section1 Configuring the AI assistant

    To configure the AI assistant:

    \list 1
      \li In the \uicontrol {AI Assistant} view, select \imagesettings.
      \li Enter the API key for your AI provider.
          \image ai-assistant-settings.webp {AI assistant settings with API key fields for each provider}
    \endlist

    Models available under a provider appear in the model selector in the
    \uicontrol {AI Assistant} view only when an API key has been entered for
    that provider. Providers without an API key are not shown in the model selector.

    You can also:

    \list
      \li Disable a provider by clearing the checkbox next to its name. Disabled
          providers and their models are removed from the model selector in the
          \uicontrol {AI Assistant} view.
      \li Reset the provider URL by selecting \imagereset next to the \uicontrol Url field.
    \endlist

    \section2 Configuring MCP servers

    During configuration, you can also go to the \uicontrol {MCP Server Settings}
    tab to configure, enable, and disable MCP servers. For details on how to
    do it, see \l{Connecting an external MCP server}.

    \section2 Adding, removing, and reorder models

    In the AI assistant settings dialog:

    \list
      \li To add another model, select \imageplus and enter the model ID for the model you want to
          add. See \l{AI models}.
      \li To remove a model, select the model and then select \imageminus.
      \li To move a model up or down, select it and use \imagenavigatorarrowup and
          \imagenavigatorarrowdown.
      \li To reset the model list to default, select \imagereset.
    \endlist

    */
